{
  "text": "In this nearshore study, evidence suggested total scavenging of both 234 Th and 90 Y at depth, and that the delivery of both nuclides and particles was controlled by convection rather than gravitational settling [CITATION_1] . Accordingly, mass fluxes were calculated as:",
